cs.NI, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.SY, cs.IT

Reasoning: 
1. cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) - The paper focuses on improving the performance and coverage of wireless networks, specifically HetNets, through resource allocation methods. 
2. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The proposed approach uses Q-learning, a type of reinforcement learning, to solve the resource allocation problem in complex networks. 
3. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The use of machine learning in the proposed approach falls under the category of AI. 
4. cs.SY (Systems and Control) - The paper discusses managing interference in HetNets, which can be seen as a control problem. 
5. cs.IT (Information Theory) - The paper considers the quality of service (QoS) for each user, which is related to information theory concepts such as channel capacity and data rate.
